  "content": "## Dependency Chain\n## Test Strategy\n\n## Industry Context\n\nApproach validates against 2025-2026 industry state:\n- **AST for code**: Universal (Cursor, Cody, cAST paper, SuperMemory)\n- **Token budget enforcement**: Every production framework (LangChain, LlamaIndex, Chonkie, Docling)\n- **Strategy/trait pattern**: Chonkie (9 strategies, one trait), Docling (template method + tokenizer interface)\n- **Recursive descent for oversized**: Universal pattern across all frameworks\n- **Overlap 10-20%**: Industry sweet spot, our 64/512 = 12.5%\n- **Sibling merging**: Cursor and cAST both use it for chunk quality\n\nUnique to Corvia: adapter-controlled split/merge callbacks for multi-domain support. No single-purpose framework needs this — Corvia does because it serves code, docs, config, and extensible domains.",
